Our financial model differs from a traditional service business because of the Asset-Based Natureof our revenue. In Year 1, we function like a lender (holding debt); in Year 2, we function like an originator (selling debt).
CORE ASSUMPTIONS
•	Capital Injection: $2,500,000 (Seed Round) deployed in Q2 2026.
•	Avg. Salary Placed: $150,000 (Growing 3% annually).
•	Success Fee Yield: $15,000 (10% of Base Salary).
•	Retainer Fee: $500/month (Avg. 4 months duration = $2,000).
•	Placement Rate: 70% (Conservative baseline; target is 80%).
•	BNPL Discount Rate: 15% (Cost of capital for selling the debt in Year 2).
